<br>
It seems to me that the priests' ability to greatly effect melee outcomes is a great deal of utility.  What tradeoffs are made for that power?  Are they getting a much better deal for surrendering DPS than other classes?<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I have argued that excess support classes should be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>adequate</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage dealers in order to be welcome on raids.  Under what circumstances are priests <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;surplus?&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I suspect that caster versus priest balance might prove more fruitful than caster versus melee.  At the very least, they are more similar, seem easier to compare, and I have seen little discussion along these lines.<br>
